    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "As mentioned in https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/pull/3827#issuecomment-1320884165, adding `indexed` is a breaking change because it changes the way the event is encoded. It is a particularly bad breaking change because it is kind of \"silent\": the event selector is not changed, but the way the data is encoded is, so clients might miss it.\r\n\r\nIf we were to change this, it needs to be coordinated with the governance tooling ecosystem, and it would need to be done along with a change to the event selector for safety.",
